<br>
I had the MM1 Grenade Launcher with max Airburst and Grenades, and the shotgun with lots of R.Slugs, but those are both slowloading weapons, which aren't really preferable against him. I think I also had an armor that gave me really good defense (it was a Tactical armor that I bought from the guy on the Heliport).<br>
<br>
I don't remember everything about this guy (I last played this game a year or two ago, back when it was brand new), but I remember that he liked to boost ram Aya and that you need to keep running around in circles, and that I need to use Protein Capsules almost every three or four hits. I also remember his doing something like making a clone that took all the damage away from him, and some sort of room-wide shockwave that drained the life from Aya. Just shoot the clone if he makes one (it should be 999 damage), and shoot the monster when the screen starts turning wavy. And STAY OFF THE BRIDGE IN THE MIDDLE. He almost always kills you if he gets in close, and the bridge is his &quot;spot,&quot; so stay away.<br>
<br>
If you can't afford the armor, or enough for the Grenade Launcher and 100 Airburst and Grenades, sad to say, you should probably start over from the beginning, because you'll only be able to find maybe four or five of the Supersoldiers to kill, and that's probably not enough money to help very much. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :hat --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/pimp.gif ALT=":hat"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><b>Gaealord Gabriel Angelo Maokai III</b>
